[2] Cholera - Kenya
Date: Tue 7 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The East African Standard (Nairobi) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200412071321.html>

Cholera kills one, 26 are hospitalized
-----------------------------------
One person died yesterday [Mon 6 Dec 2004], and 26 others were
admitted to Voi Hospital, following an outbreak of cholera in the
area.
The District Medical Officer of Health, Dr. Shem Pata, confirmed the
death and said a consignment of drugs had been dispatched to the
affected areas. He said the government had also put medical personnel
on high alert following the outbreak of the disease.
Pata said in his office at Wundanyi District Hospital that 6 people
at Voi and Maungu had been diagnosed and confirmed to be suffering
from cholera, while 20 others were under observation at Voi District
Hospital after showing symptoms of the disease.
He said the deceased was a patient from Mtito Andei, where the
disease was 1st reported last week [1st week of December 2004]. The
doctor said long distance drivers between Mombasa and Malaba were to
blame for the spread of the disease. He said 1500 people, who had
been in contact with cholera patients, have been given anti-cholera
drugs.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

