[3] Diarrhea - Bangladesh
Date: Mon 20 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The New Nation [edited]
<http://nation.ittefaq.com/artman/publish/article_14717.shtml>

Diarrhea epidemic - 5 die in Dinajpur
-------------------------------------
Diarrhea has become an epidemic in Sadar, Biral and Birampur Upazila,
where more than 2000 people have come down with the disease.
At least 5 of them died in 24 hours on Mon 20 Dec 2004. Health
officials confirmed the death of 2 adults, aged 55 and 60, and 2
children, aged 3 and 7, in Dinajpur Medical College Hospital.
Some 40 people attacked by the disease were admitted to Dinajpur
Medical College Hospital on 20 Dec 2004. More than 100 people were
undergoing treatment at Birampur Health Complex. MP Maulana Azizur
Rahman and Birampur UNO Sayed Noor Alam found acute shortages of
saline and other medicines while visiting the affected areas. They
have sent an urgent message to the authority for immediate dispatch
of the medicines.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
