[4] Dysentery - Russia (Siberia)
Date: Wed 22 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Russian news agency Press-Line [edited]
<http://www.press-line.ru/?action=3Donenews*news_id=3D31315>

Dysentery, Krasnoyarsk region, Russia
-------------------------------------
In the Lazarevo settlement of the Abanskiy area, in the Krasnoyarsk
region, 15 persons, including 6 children, were ill with dysentery
from 3-21 Dec 2004, stated the Siberian regional center of the
Ministry of Emergency Measures.
10 persons, including 6 children, have been hospitalized in the
infectious disease branch of the central regional hospital. 2
children (one-and-a-half-years old and one-month-old) have died. The
diagnosis has been confirmed by the laboratory. Experts from the
state center for sanitary and epidemiological supervision for the
Abanskiy area are carrying out an investigation to determine the
reasons for the outbreak.
[The Krasnoyarsk Region is located in the southern part of Siberia. - Mod.NR]
