[5] Diarrhea - Russia (Maritime Region)
Date: Mon 27 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Itar-Tass.com [edited]
<http://www.itar-tass.com/eng/level2.html?NewsID=1602134&PageNum=0>

Numerous enteric infection cases registered in Maritime region
-----------------------------------------------
A total of 107 people have fallen ill with enteric infection in
Russia's Maritime region over the past week [3rd week of December
2004]. Medics believe that impure water and low-quality diary
products are behind the outbreak of the disease.
Sources from the regional sanitary and epidemiological service told
Tass, on Mon 27 Dec 2004, that dozens of cases had been registered in
Vladivostok, Nakhodka, Spassk-Dalny, and Ussuriisk, as well as in 4
districts of the Maritime region.
Ahead of the New Year holidays, specialists urge local residents to
drink only boiled or bottled water, to use only fresh diary products,
as well as to thermally treat cottage cheese and milk.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
