[6] Dysentery - Russia (Karachayevo-Cherkessia)
Date: 17 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail correspondent Vadim Melnik <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Rian.ru news agency, 17 Dec 2004 [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.rian.ru/rian/intro.cfm?nws_id=763375>

An outbreak of dysentery, type _Shigella sonnei_ (shigellosis), has
been reported in the south region of Karachayevo-Cherkessia. 71
people are hospitalized; 55 of them are children. The outbreak was
due to consumption of impure milk products.
[Karachayevo-Cherkessia borders Chechnya. - Mod.LL]
